</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="BrullÃ©">Brulle</normalizedToken>
, 1838 by original designation. Etymology. From the Greek 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="781" pageNumber="782">anchone</emphasis>
(strangling) and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="781" pageNumber="782">dere</emphasis>
